                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Protective Prayers</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <title ref="LIT6845PPSatolay" type="incomplete">Prayer against the pain caused by Tǝgrǝtyā, Šotalāy and Šotalāyt</title>
                            <note>In comparison to the attestation in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr32#ms_i1"/>, the incipit in this scroll is 
                                shorter and directed not only against Šotalāy and Šotalāyt, but also against Tǝgrǝtyā.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ትግርትያ፡ ወሾተላይ፡ ወሾተላይት፡ ዘትቀትል፡ ሕፃናተ፡
                                እምሐልኩከ፡ ወአውገዝኩከ፡ ወአሰርኩከ፡ ወለጐምኩከ፡ ከመ፡ ኢትቅትል፡ ሕፃናተ፡ ኃተምኩከ፡ በማኅተመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩ አምላክ፡ 
                                አሰርኩከ፡ አንተ፡ ሾተላይ፡ ወሾተላይት፡ በዝንተ፡ አስማት፡ መአጁን፡ መአጁን፡ ፈቃጁ፡ መጂር፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <title ref="LIT7601PPSalomon"/>
                            <note>In comparison to the attestation in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr32#ms_i2"/>, the incipit in this scroll is 
                                shorter and the name of Šotalāyt was omitted.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ሰሎሞን፡ ሎፍሐም፡ ንምሎስ፡ ዮፍታሔ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> አምሐልኩከ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> 
                                አንተ፡ ጋኔን፡ ሾተላይ፡ ከመ፡ <supplied reason="lost">ኢትቅርቡ፡</supplied> ኀበ፡ ነፍሳ፡ ወሥጋሃ፡ ለዓመትከ፡ <gap reason="lost"/>
                                    </incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <title ref="LIT6609ProtectPrayer">Prayer against pains caused by Zār, Tǝgrǝtyā, Bāryā and Legewon, Dask and Gudāle</title>
                            <note>The incipit contains <term key="MagicSymbols">magic glyphs (charaktêres)</term>. Similar to 
                                <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr32#ms_i3"/>, this prayer is also directed against Zār, Bāryā, Dask, Legewon and Gudāle,
                                but it also targets Tǝgrǝtyā.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> አድኅና፡ እምሕማመ፡ ዛር፡ ወትግርትያ፡ ባርያ፡ ወሌጌዎን፡ ደስክ፡ ወጕዳሌ፡ ወኵሉ፡ ደዌ፡
                                ለአመትከ፡ <gap reason="lost"/></incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <title ref="LIT7872Tegretya"/><!-- Issue #3342 -->
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ትግርትያ፡ ተሰደዱ፡ በሰሀለል፡ ትግርትያ፡ ተአሰሩ፡ ሎኤ፡ ሎኤ፡ ሎኤ፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                            <title ref="LIT4622Prayer"/>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ቁርፀት፡ ዘተፈተወት፡ እምኀበ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ከመ፡ ይርዳእ፡ ወይቤዙ፡ ለውሉደ፡ እጓለ፡ እመሕያው፡ እንዘ፡ 
                                ይበጸብጽ፡ ከርሠ፡ ወይጐጸንጕጽ፡ ገበዋተ፡ ወይጠዊ፡ አንጀተ፡ ወቈነጥን፡ አማዑተ፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡ ሽገር፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                            <title ref="LIT4705MagicPr"/>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ <surplus>በእንተ፡</surplus> ሕማመ፡ ውግዓት፡ አላህ፡ መላህ፡ በላህ፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i7">
                            <title ref="LIT4620Prayer"/>
                            <note>In contrast to its attestation in <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet77"/>, the text of this scroll is directed only against
                                blacksmiths, but not against demons (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾagānǝnt</foreign>).</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ነሃብት፡ አላሁማ፡ ወያኑራ፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i8">
                            <title ref="LIT7873Spirits"/><!-- Issue #3343 -->
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> አጁር፡ ናኤሆር፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ ይትኃረድ፡
                                ይትኃረድ፡ ይትኃረድ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ይቤሎ፡ አገዝኩ፡ ለዝ፡ ጋኔን፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> በዝ፡ ቃልከ፡ ተአሠሩ፡ መናፍስተ፡ ርኩሳን፡
                                ወሰብእ፡ መሠርያን፡ እምላእለ፡ አመትከ፡ <gap reason="lost"/></incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i9">
                            <title ref="LIT5135MagicFormula"/>
                            <note>The text in this scroll is entitled <foreign xml:lang="gez">Ṣalota ḥǝmāma karś</foreign> 
                                (‘Prayer against ache of the stomach’), while the text in another attestation in <ref type="mss" corresp="IVEf45"/> is 
                                directed against <foreign xml:lang="gez">qʷǝrṣat</foreign>, which can also be interpreted as ‘stomach ache’.
                                The end is missing.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">አልፍሉል፡ አልፍሉል፡ አልፍሉል፡ ጸሎተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ከርሥ፡ 
                                ዘይደ<supplied reason="omitted" resp="PRS8999Strelcyn">ነ</supplied>ጕዝ፡ ገበዋተ፡ ወይጠዊ፡ ወይሰብር፡ አንጀተ፡ ወአማዑተ፡
                                    </incipit>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="Scroll">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><material key="parchment"/></support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure unit="leaf" quantity="1">1</measure>
                                    <measure unit="strips" quantity="2">2</measure>
                                    <note>Scroll originally consisting of at least three strips. The third strip is missing,  while traces of stitching are 
                                        visible along the bottom edge of the second strip.</note>
                                    <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                                        <height>935</height>
                                        <width>85</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <condition key="deficient">The bottom part of the scroll is missing. The manuscript is torn in two places in its lower 
                                    section. The upper edges of the first strip have been damaged by sweat, and the ends of several lines are illegible. The 
                                    same applies to the first two lines, which are written in red.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc><handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                            <seg type="script">Careful, angular script.</seg>
                            <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote xml:id="d1">
                                <note>At the top of the scroll, the lower part of a <term key="MagicDrawing">magic drawing</term> is visible.</note>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <desc>On the verso side of the scroll, at the bottom part, a note by <persName ref="PRS3182ContiRo" role="owner"/>,
                                        stating that the manuscript was given from <persName ref="PRS15459Celoria" role="owner">
                                            <roleName type="rank">tenente</roleName> Candido Celoria</persName> to 
                                        <persName ref="PRS15458Rey" role="owner"><roleName type="rank">Generale</roleName> Felice Rey
                                            </persName>.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="it">Donato dal tenente Celoria al gen. Rey nel 1895</q>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1895">Nineteenth century</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The first owner of the scroll was a person, whose name was probably 
                            <persName ref="PRS15456WalattaMi" role="owner">Walatta Mikāʾel</persName>.
                            Her name was replaced by that of another woman, 
                            <persName ref="PRS15457WalattaMad" role="owner">Walatta Madḫǝn</persName>, 
                            whose name was written in black.</provenance>
                    </history>
